<font color=#333399>(6/5/01 10:16:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Epic questions</span><hr size=1> A few questions for you lucky devils with the leafy sword.<br>
<br>
How fast is the recovery time on the proc (Wrath of Nature)? Ie, how quickly can you recast it.<br>
<br>
I read that it's a snare proc. Is that the same snare as the Ensnare we use when quadding, ie it slows them, or is it more like a root, or does it not slow the mobs at all?<br>
<br>
I understand the damage is around 1700. Is it immediate or over time? If over time, how long?<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugroovydancepants.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GroovyDancepants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 1:07:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic questions</span><hr size=1> Immediate recast. Slow casting time. Overrides ensnare and slows movement rate by about the same. 1650 damage over time. Lasts 3 minutes and snare effect is same duration as damage. It stacks with all your other dots. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ushanarwolfinator.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ShanarWolfinator</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 5:37:56 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic questions</span><hr size=1> It would be quite insane if it was 1700 immediate damage =) I would never have to group again! bwahaha <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=caraddor>Caraddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 5:22:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic questions</span><hr size=1> Groovy covered it pretty well.  Only thing I can add is you can cast the proc before your spell icons refresh.  For instance, if you root mob x, you can immediately start the proc cast even though all your spell icons are grayed out for that second or two.<br>
<br>
It's a long dot (does an estimated 53 damage per tick over 3 minutes), so root/dotting strictly with the epic takes a while, but can be done.<br>
<br>
Some things to keep in mind:  <br>
<br>
  - Engulfing Roots can last 3 minutes.  If you root a mob close to the same time you epic dot him, they can both wear off close to the same time.  I avoid that by refreshing the epic dot every minute or so.  It's no fun to have an unsnared mob after you.<br>
<br>
 - The epic will overwrite ensnare, and ensnare will not overwrite epic<br>
<br>
 - There is no casting time meter that shows up when casting epic, so if you're not close enough to see the 'so and so just had a bad day' message, you won't be sure when you're done casting (you can get around that by trying to use other hotkeys and waiting for the 'you cannot use this command' message to stop)<br>
<br>
Hope this helps<br>
<br>
Caraddor (Order of the Scattered Winds)<br>
52 Wanderer<br>
Bertoxx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugalaintreeavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galain Treeavenger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 5:41:00 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://kazzakhan.homestead.com/files/Talionis_07.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Epic questions</span><hr size=1> Correct, if you are too far away you do not get a success message, but you do get a resist message if it fails.  I just watch for the particle effect on the mob or the fail message to determine if I need to redo it.<br>
<br>
As for damage, Groovy is right.  It does 1650 damage over 3 minutes.  This works out to 550/minute = 55/tick since a tick is 6 seconds. <p><HR>
